HEADWORD: Over-arm
<hw>O"ver-arm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Cricket,
etc.)</fld> <def>Done (as bowling or pitching) with the arm raised above
the shoulder. See <er>Overhard</er>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>over-arm</xex>
with a round-arm bowler.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>R. A. Proctor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

